s a delectable assortment of poetry, prose, and essays, and the selections all include at least one tempting recipe to entice readers to cook this book. Including writing from such notables as Maya Angelou, James Beard, Alice B. Toklas, Sherman Alexie, Nora Ephron, M.F.K. Fisher, and Alice Waters, among many others, Books That Cook reveals the range of ways authors incorporate recipes-whether the recipe flavors the story or the story serves to add spice to the recipe. Books That Cook is a collection to serve students and teachers of food studies as well as any epicure who enjoys a good meal alongside a good book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCooking in literature. 0aFood in literature. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aCognard-Black, Jennifer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNestle, Marion, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071187540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479838424423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479838424.jpg  a978-3-11-071187-5  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK